## Common Mistakes and Fixes

| Mistake                              | Fix                                      |
| ------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------- |
| `Number(amount) / 1e18`              | `formatUnits(amount, decimals)`          |
| `Number(value) / 10 ** USD_DECIMALS` | `formatUnits(value, USD_DECIMALS)`       |
| `parseUnits(amount, 18)`             | `parseUnits(amount, tokenData.decimals)` |
| `amount.toString()` math             | Keep in BigInt, use operators            |
| `parseFloat(amount) * 0.005`         | `(amount * 5n) / 1000n`                  |

## Key Principle

> **Always use the token's actual decimals. Never assume 18.**  
> **Always use USD_DECIMALS constant for USD values. Never hardcode 1e9 or 1e18.**  
> **LLMs see the formatted values, not the bigints. Format correctly to prevent confusion.**
